article.headline: High Point 75, Chowan 59
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Jefferson scored 16 points and had eight assists to lead High Point to a 75-59 win over Chowan on Wednesday. Arizona Reid added 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Panthers (3-2), who shot 48 percent from the floor. Trayvon Lathan led the Hawks (1-2) with 17 points, and Deon Tynes had 13 points and 10 rebounds. The game was suspended when the power went out Tuesday night with High Point leading 41-33 with 17 seconds left in the first half. Play resumed Wednesday, and High Point outscored Chowan 12-4 in the opening minutes of the second half to build a 16-point lead of 53-37. The Panthers led by double digits for the remainder of the game, and twice led by 19 points.
